Angola to Offer Its First Sovereign Bond, Worth $500 Million, in September

-- B y   C a n d i d o   M e n d e s
-- 
2011-04-20T18:15:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/angola-to-offer-its-first-sovereign-bond-worth-500-million-in-september.html
Angola plans to offer its first
dollar-denominated sovereign bond, worth $500 million, in
September, Finance Minister Carlos Alberto Lopes said.  The country has paid $2.2 billion of its domestic debt as
of January, mainly to Portuguese and Brazilian building
companies, Lopes told reporters in Luanda, the capital, today.
Another $2.5 billion is outstanding, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Candido Mendes in Luanda at 
